didate D: problem solving, responsibility, concentration, handles unexpected events, but moody, loner, arrogant, weak leadership. Teamwork likely poor.\n\nThus candidate C seems to have strong decision making, calm, concern for others (teamwork), attention skills, but communication difficulty and egocentric may hinder. However concern for others may indicate good crew cooperation despite egocentric? Might be contradictory.\n\nCandidate A has leadership but unfriendly and unorganized.\n\nCandidate B technical but communication poor.\n\nCandidate D reliability strong but teamwork poor.\n\nThus likely best is Candidate C? Need to weigh seriousness: communication issues are serious for crew coordination. Egocentric also serious. But concern for others may mitigate. Candidate A's unfriendliness also serious. Unorganized could affect reliability. Candidate B's nasty remarks also serious. Candidate D's moody and loner also serious.\n\nWhich candidate has least severe negatives? Candidate C's negatives: difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric, not willing to further education. But he puts concern for others above everything, which suggests teamwork orientation. Also excellent attention skills, quick correct decisions, calm. That seems balanced.\n\nThus I will vote Candidate C.\n\nNow produce public message: summarize evaluation, note missing info (e.g., actual teamwork observations), maybe ask others for more on candidate strengths we lack (e.g., leadership of D, B's technical depth, A's reliability). Provide reasoning."}
